andard sized banner) the post <i>will be</i> edited so that the signature is removed. <br><br><li>If your sig widens the thread so much that someone has to use the bottom (horizontal) scrollbar to go back and forth reading from the front to the end of the line on a standard 15' monitor, it is too big.<br><br><li>Please try to keep sigs (whole sig) under 25kb, and the whole signature and images included shouldn't be much larger than the standard banner.<br><br><li>We do host images for signatures if you need it.  Send to <a href="mailto:darkflame@allakhazam.com"><font color=magenta>Darkflame</font></a>  Large images will be denied or altered.<br><br><br><big><font color=yellow><u>Instructions</u></font></big><br>for sigs, icons, and personal pics.<br>(Ok, I am not a professional and input to help out is appreciated) <br><br><br>Firstly...all pictures you wish to have on your account must be hosted somewhere else and the URL (internet address) linked to your ezboard account. Make sure the place that you have your images hosted allows remote linking, most do not, ie Tripod, Geocities, Yahoo etc do not.<br><br>Secondly...how to.<br><br>1) Picture that appears under your EZ board name. <br><br>From our guild's message board go to My Control Center. Under my profile go to edit profile. Then add your URL to the space given under "personal photo URL" it should look like this: "http://whatever.com/images/filename.fileext" An example would be "http://gelle.com/images/gelle.jpg" or something similar depending on where the photo file is located (without quotes and these are fake btw). After you add the address make sure that you check the little box that says "Use personal photo." After EZ board connects to your pic it will show in your profile.<br><br>2) Personal icon.<br><br>From our guild's message board go to My Control Center. Under my profile go to edit preferences. Then scroll down to "personal icon." Just as above add the URL to the icon you wish to use. If you wish to use one of EZ boards icons click on the red text that says "use one of ours." Either way, it should look like the example above. Make sure you check the box that says "Use personal icon next to my user name."<br><br>3) Custom Signature<br><br>This one is a little bit tougher, considering on what you want to put here. If all you want to do is put your name here, then do so. But if you want to add a little saying, do so and remember to put the break tag (see guide or cheatsheet for more info on break tag) in where you want it to go to the next line or it will run together. The instructions are above the area for the text. If you have a small pic and do not want to size it, you can list an address here as above. However...if you need to change the size of it or make a creative signature, ie. colors, italics, make a link etc, you will need a little HTML. I could give a little HTML lesson here, but what a pain in the butt, hehe So if you want something special like mine...e mail me and I will write the script for you and mail it back, along with a little explanation of what I did. But if you feel the urge to create a masterpiece on your own, here is a <a href="http://hotwired.lycos.com/webmonkey/authoring/html_basics/"><font color=red>little guide</font></a> and <a href="http://hotwired.lycos.com/webmonkey/reference/html_cheatsheet/"><font color=red>cheatsheet</font></a>. If you need somewhere to host a pic let someone know and we will do what we can to get it done for you. As always don't forget to check the box that says, "Use custom signature."<br><br>I hope this helps whomever may need it. If I failed at my attempt EZ board has a <a href="http://login.ezboard.com/bezboard"><font color=lime>help section</font></a> just for this information. <br><li><a href="http://www.ezboard.com/help/help_howto_customsignature.html">Custom sig help</a><br><li><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/fcooltipsntricksfrm1.showMessage?topicID=20.topic">Glowing T