ake your custom signature.<br>About halfway down the page is a box with the heading of &quot;custom signature&quot;<br>In here is where you type out what you want added to every post you make on an ezboard.<br>You CANNOT use EZCODES. Signatures MUST be in HTML. And as I found out, HTML comments are NOT allowed and they will ERASE your ENTIRE custom signature.<br><br>If you are using an image in your custom signature, the proper code to use is:<br>&lt;img src=&quot;<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.mysite/my/path/myfile">">www.mysite/my/path/myfile"></a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>where mysite is your web host. my/path/ is the directory to your file and myfile is the image.<br><br>After you have put everything into the sig that you want, make sure that &quot;include custom signature&quot; is checked underneath the text box. This will automatically check the box under your posts to include your signature. If you leave this box unchecked, you must manually check to put your sig in each post you make.<br><br>Some boards don't allow custom signatures, most do. Some have size limits on images. Make sure to learn the rules of boards before posting your new sig everywhere, it could get you in trouble.<br><br>Also...<br><br>If you want to make something show up on the next line, you can't just hit enter in the box, you need to use the &lt;br&gt; tag for each line you want it to skip. Just for an example, I'll post my sig and explain it...<br><br>&lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2398"><img src="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/images/characters/Muse/lizzie-sig2.jpg" width="400" height="149" border="0"></a>&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://companions.windsofstorm.net/images/quotes/06-05-01.jpg"><br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;<a href="http://companions.windsofstorm.net/">%lt;The Companions></a>&lt;br&gt;<br><a href="http://www.thetribunal.org">Tribunal Server</a>&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> &lt;div align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>This centers anything between the two tags. You can also use &lt;center&gt;&lt;/center&gt;<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2398"></a><br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>This makes anything between the two tags hyperlink to my magelo profile, replace the http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=2398 with whatever you want to link to.<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> &lt;img src=&quot;http://companions.windsofstorm.net/images/characters/Muse/lizzie-sig2.jpg" width=&quot;400&quot; height=&quot;149&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;&gt;<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>In my sig, I chose to link an image to the magelo profile. You don't need to put in the width=&quot;x&quot; height=&quot;y&quot;, but it helps the browser to decide how big it is in the content sooner. The border=&quot;0&quot; keeps the image from having a line around it which will happen otherwise if you put a link tag around an image tag.<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> &lt;br&gt;<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>Tells the browser to insert a line break. If you need two line breaks you can use &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;, etc. This tag does not need a closing tag ( &lt;/br&gt;).<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> &lt;font face=&quot;Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif&quot; size=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>Any text between these two tags will be Verdana, size 1. If your computer doesn't have Verdana, it will use Arial or the next font in sequence that it *does* have. If you use a funky fon't that's on your computer, but you're not sure others have it, make sure to include some alternate choices.<br><br><br>Quote:<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> %lt;The Companions&gt;<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br><br>Okay, this is to put your guild in the funky &lt; &gt; brackets. If you use a &lt; instead of the %lt; It won't show your guild name at all, it will think it's an HTML tag and the browser ignores it because it doesn't know what it is.<br><br>Good luck.  I hope this helps...the html is from old server.dont mind it.<br> <p><br><img src="http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/shawn_olsen/fullsize/ofyst.jpg"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/udarkflameassassin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkflame Assassin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/kinariudfalivae/images/ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><marquee><big><font color=magenta >Board Goddess</font></big></marquee><br></span><br>  Posts: 491<br> <font color=#7C61AB>(3/26/02 3:30:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/flegends11114frm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID